
Materials in this directory pertain to "The Little Schemer", 4th Edition,
by Daniel P. Friedman and Matthias Felleisen (drawings by Duane Bibby,
foreword by Gerald J. Sussman).  This book was published in December 1995
(ISBN# 978-0-262-56099-3).

Chapters in the book are:

    1. Toys
    2. 
    3. Cons the Magnificent
    4. 
    5.
    6.
    7.
    8. Lambda the Ultimate
    9.
   10. What Is the Value of All of This?

A URI for the book (as of 20 Oct. 2007) is
"http://www.ccs.neu.edu/home/matthias/BTLS/".  There is only one entry in
the errata at this point:

>>> Lars Gregori points out that contrary to page 156 in the book, Wilhelm
>>> Ackermann lived from 1896 to 1962. His sources are:
>>>    http://www-groups.dcs.st-andrews.ac.uk/history/Mathematicians/Ackermann.html
>>>    http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wilhelm_Ackermann

Files and directories are:

   README      this file
   Makefile    test targets and other build commands
   ex/         answers to The Little Lisper, plus unit tests
   lib/        Scheme functions
   misc/       other related files
   t/          unit tests for functions defined in the book and in-book
               exercises; read TESTING below

TESTING

Tests use the TAP protocol and the "runtests" script provided by Perl
module "TAP::Harness".


